{
  "texts": [
    "All such techniques freeze the pre-trained model, but differ in the location of the inserted trainable parameters.",
    "We focus specifically on Bottleneck adapters and on Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA).",
    "Bottleneck adapters [10] have a structure similar to autoencoders.",
    "The transformer hidden state h is first down-projected to some smaller dimensionality d bottleneck with matrix W down, passes through non-linearity function f, and is then up-projected to the original dimensionality with matrix W up, and a residual connection r. This is defined formally in Eq 1.",
    "The location of the adapter layer depends on the adapter type."
  ]
}